    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "I'm Niles from the Kingdom of Nohr. Former outlaw. Current disgrace. My arrows are yours.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "That weapon of yours has such a provocative shape. Does it feel good to fire it? I bet it does.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I serve Lord Leo. He rescued me from my former existence as a filthy thief. I'd give my life for him.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "If you run yourself ragged, you should be sure to take a nap. I'd be tickled to show you where.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "How about a midnight stroll at some point? I won't bite. I never do. At least, not by the light of the moon.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "That prince you serve is a pretty bit of porcelain. But I think he'd look nicer with a few chips.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "You must be <Player Name>. Someone must be awfully fond of you to send me all this way. And that... is <Friend Name>!",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "My gain will be another's pain.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I deserve better.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "How unfortunate.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "Oh! You've taken some liberties with me. How nice.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "Here you are. And here I am! Aren't we a pair. I must confess that I've grown after each of your visits—really and truly, I have! I must also say that when I first met you, Summoner, I thought you were a fussy bit of butter. I served you, but not happily. But now! Oh, what a difference! I long to always be with you. I wonder, have you only indulged your servant Niles? Or are we becoming friends now? I know some see me as unsavory. To them I say, variety is the spice of life! But, what say you? Eh? You trust me? How curious. Someone dear to me once said the very same thing. So, you and I will be friends through thick and thin. And, you know me... I always delight my friends.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
